This paper is about improving multilingual neural machine translation (MNMT) for low-resource languages (LRL) using data selection and model adaptation. The paper focuses on language modeling and natural language processing, which are subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques such as neural networks, which are also relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions using image data for translation, which could be relevant to sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision).
